oung as your self-confidence, as old as your fear; as young as your hope, as old as your despair.' Douglas MacArthur\n\n- Terri  Marie, The Shack, Merry and a Cat Named Cha-moan\n|\nBack in my day, which was about a week and a half ago, we took our lumps and we got back up and we cried like babies and quit and then put on weight.\n\n- Joss Whedon, Buffy the Vampire Slayer: The Long Way Home, Part 3\n|\nHave I told you I love you?' he whispers.I smile. 'Not since this morning.''Unforgivable. I will tell you every hour of every day.\n\n- Jessica Khoury, The Forbidden Wish\n|\nFirst Pallas and now you,” the gray-haired man said, shaking his head at Nick. “It’s like I’m running a goddamn dating service around here.\n\n- Julie James, A Lot like Love\n|\nknowledge is infnite , time is limited ,sucess is temprary so enlighten your soul before leaving it..\n\n- Vivek\n|\nDialogue is about creating awareness through self-observation; it starts from the inside out, not the outside in.\n\n- Oli Anderson, Dialogue / Ego - Real Communication\n|\nIn time of poverty, you alone face is your fate. If your spirit is stronger enough, you will survive.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nDie, die we all pass away, But don't wear a frown coz it's really okay,And you might try to hide, And you might try to pray,But we all end up remains of the day.\n\n- Danny\n|\nPatriotism, when it wants to make itself felt in the domain of learning, is a dirty fellow who should be thrown out of doors.\n\n- Arthur\n|\nThe Great Depression, like most other periods of severe unemployment, was produced by government mismanagement rather than by any inherent instability of the private economy.\n\n- Milton\n|\nWhen I see my mom in the stands, it always pushes me to succeed.\n\n- Ashton\n|\nChange is inevitable. And in a way, change is a sort of magic. However, not everyone believes in something as frugal as the unexplained.\n\n- Katlyn Charlesworth, Where Men Sit\n|\nThe day you stop caring about opinions of other , is the first day of you freedom.\n\n- Robin\n|\nChange is fearful, but at the end it is beautiful.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhen a man cheats, it is said it is because he is a dog. When a woman cheats, it is said it is because her man is a dog.\n\n- Mokokoma Mokhonoana, Divided & Conquered\n|\nWhen I escape from my cage of conformity, I grow wings to fly in search of truth and beauty.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI have always been a fire, and everyone I loved walked away as ashes, until I met a phoenix who was born to love flames.\n\n- Jenim Dibie, The Calligraphy of God\n|\nLet your children nourish their knack, for that knack shall one day provide them with the way to live with dignity and contentment.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Human Making is Our Mission: A Treatise on Parenting\n|\nIn a society as broken as ours, 'antisocial' behavior is the only behavior worth defending.\n\n- Lauren McLaughlin, Scored\n|\nThey call what we went through a problem, an experience, a dream… but we know that it’s much more than that.\n\n- Emory R. Frie, Wonderland\n|\nDo you know how when you're moving really fast in a car, and you're looking at the road, you get sick, but if you look at the trees you're fine? She's my trees, man.\n\n- Rebecca Timberlake, Bookish Hearts"